channel.title: Possible Tattoo Designs
channel.description:
My birthday is coming soon, so I was thinking about getting a tattoo. I grabbed a pencil and started scribbling away, and I would appreciate some feedback on the outcomes. Yep, I'm a wannabe artist.
First, here's an old thing I did when I was at school: ![](upload://wWHlVYxph3EriKUqPemkJ1kDCoU.png) An ice heart. I used a sharpie to draw the lines, scanned it, and then colored it in PhotoImpression. The wings look awful and pixellated because I drew them separately on notebook paper and had to digitally remove the lines later. Besides, they were much smaller than the heart itself. I personally think the design is way too big, and those colors would surely make the price go up. I don't have much money, and that's certainly a problem.
Then the most recent designs come up. Here is something small: ![](upload://2PWGAiSQtK4FMg9MLjTXzYWFVaL.png) A stylized old-style F-clef. I love music, so I thought about getting a bass clef tattoo, but then I noticed it has been done to death. I did some research and found [url='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Oldbassclef.svg']this[/url] design. It was love at first sight. Simple, and most certainly, cheap.
And then, the real point of this thread: ![](upload://6WzxwIXNVcJU6i4n02wsoKjhGZP.png) A Half-Life themed tattoo for my ankle. This is the one I would LOVE feedback about. I took the flames from Photostock (lazy, I know, I didn't even remove the watermark completely), and then added he lambda into the mix. I really, really like it, but I think some comments would be nice, since the design itself would be a pain in the neck to cover later on. What do you guys think?

item.dc:creator: raw_bean
item.description:
Lamsey:

I’m not sure that tattoing yourself with Dark Speech is such a good idea. Your arm would probably take on a life of its own and start randomly punching you in the face.

Actually, now I want to tattoo my arm with Black Speech just so I can start punching people with it and claim it’s not my fault because it’s possessed. I can voluntarily make my eyes and eyelids spasm, so I could do that while reciting (from memory) ‘Azh nazh durbataluk, azh nazh gimbatul, azh nazh thrakataluk, agh burzum izhi krimpatul!’

It’ll all be good fun until someone tries to perform an exorcism on me.
